Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,537,1563]" box="[312,855,1257,1283]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,644,1257,1283]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[651,704,1257,1283]" name="Peru" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[761,851,1257,1283]" name="Bolivia" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,537,1563]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,683,1297,1323]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Derivation of specific epithet.</emphasis>
Latin 
<emphasis box="[762,819,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">pilus</emphasis>
for hair and 
<emphasis box="[977,1065,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">dorsum</emphasis>
for back, referring to the dorsally setose ovipositor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
